.TH hsh 1 "July 29, 2022" "1" "Holberton Simple Shell"

.SH NAME

.B Simple_shell -- hsh
- A simple command line interpreter for linux

.SH SYNOPSIS
This shell mimics /bin/sh in it's funcationaly. It can be ran in both interacitve and noninteractive modes.

.SH DESCRIPTION

This shell functions as a simple UNIX command line interpreter. This shell will display a prompt ($ ) and wait for the user to type a command that always ends with a new line
The prompt will be displayed again each time a command has been executed.
The command lines will be simple, with no semicolons, pipes, redirections, or other advanced features.
If an executable cannot be found, and error message will be printed and the prompt will be displayed.
This shell will handle errors, and handle the "end of file" condition Ctrl+D.

.SH BUILTINS

The following builtin commands are supported:

.IT
.B env
- prints the current environment

.B exit
- exits the program with no arguments passed

.SS Usage Example
.RS
After compilation and executaion via ./hsh
.P
$ echo Hello, world!
.P
Hello, world!

